In your second snippet of code

```
for(int start = scan.nextInt();start&lt;=(start+10);start++)
{
    System.out.println(start);
}
```

You&#39;re comparing `start` to itself plus 10. Regardless what operation you&#39;re going to perform, nothing can&#39;t be equals to itself plus 10. `start` will always be lower than itself plus 10 and therefore producing an infinite loop. &lt;b&gt;It&#39;s a semantic error.&lt;/b&gt; You should use a different variable to keep track of the loop, as you did in your first snippet, and a second one for the confrontation (`start` in your case).

