I&#39;ve found solution here https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25909611/eclipse-dynamic-web-module-3-0-requires-java-1-6-or-newer-error-while-creating

Adding the next lines to the pom.xml helped in my case

```
    &lt;plugins&gt;
        &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;source&gt;1.8&lt;/source&gt;
                &lt;target&gt;1.8&lt;/target&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/plugin&gt;
    &lt;/plugins&gt;
```

In your *pom.xml* file add these properties:

    &lt;project xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0&quot; xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot; xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd&quot;&gt;
    	...
    	&lt;properties&gt;
    		&lt;maven.compiler.source&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.source&gt;
    		&lt;maven.compiler.target&gt;17&lt;/maven.compiler.target&gt;
    	&lt;/properties&gt;
    	...
    &lt;/project&gt;

Here I use **JDK-17**, but you should change it to installed version of *JDK*.

And after that, right click on your project and choose **Maven &gt; Update Project...**

Then you can select newer versions of *Dynamic Web Module*.

