As others have already mentioned, it depends on the OS.

- For 32-bit Windows:  it&#39;ll be &lt;2GB  ([Windows internals book][1] says 2GB for user processes)
- For 32-bit BSD / Linux:  &lt;3GB       (from the [Devil Book][2])
- For 32-bit MacOS X: &lt;4GB            (from [Mac OS X internals][3] book)
- Not sure about 32-bit Solaris, but the code above [has been tested in this answer][4].

For a 64-bit host OS, if the JVM is 32-bit, it&#39;ll still depend, most likely like above as demonstrated.

